    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Cut your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into chips, then add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking paper-lined baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/flat-iron-steak-creamed-spinach-smoked-salt-chips-and-gravy/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can \u2013 this is your <strong>blanched spinach</strong></p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic </strong>open by squashing it with the side of a knife and discard the skin</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/flat-iron-steak-creamed-spinach-smoked-salt-chips-and-gravy/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>blanched spinach </strong>to a<strong> food processor </strong>with your <strong>crushed garlic</strong></p><p>Add a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, a small splash of <strong>water </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Blitz until smooth \u2013 this is your<strong> blitzed spinach</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/flat-iron-steak-creamed-spinach-smoked-salt-chips-and-gravy/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>blitzed spinach </strong>to a pot with your <strong>clotted cream </strong>and <strong>most </strong>of<strong> </strong>your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(save some for a topping!) and <strong>half </strong>your <strong>smoked salt</strong> (you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Cook over a medium heat for 3-4 min or until bubbling and thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>creamed spinach</strong></p><p>Set aside, off the heat (you'll reheat it later!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/flat-iron-steak-creamed-spinach-smoked-salt-chips-and-gravy/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle and heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Pat your <strong>flat iron steak[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper, then drizzle them with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season with a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> on both sides</p><p>Once very hot, add the <strong>flat iron steak[s]</strong> to the pan</p><p>For rare, cook for 2-3 min max on each side; for medium-rare, cook for 3-4 min on each side; for medium, cook for 4-5 min on each side</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/flat-iron-steak-creamed-spinach-smoked-salt-chips-and-gravy/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the steak[s] is cooked, transfer to a clean board to rest for 3-4 min and reserve the pan</p><p>Combine your <strong>gravy base</strong> with 125ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and whisk thoroughly \u2013 this is your <strong>gravy mix</strong></p><p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat, then add your <strong>gravy mix </strong>and cook for 1-2 min, stirring regularly, or until thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>gravy</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/flat-iron-steak-creamed-spinach-smoked-salt-chips-and-gravy/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the <strong>creamed spinach</strong> to a medium heat with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until bubbling</p><p>Slice the <strong>rested steak</strong> finely</p><p>Once the chips are ready, season with the <strong>remaining smoked salt</strong> and give them a good mix up \u2013 these are your <strong>smoked salt chips</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/flat-iron-steak-creamed-spinach-smoked-salt-chips-and-gravy/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> sliced steak </strong>and drizzle over the<strong> gravy</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>creamed spinach </strong>and sprinkle over the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>smoked salt chips </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
